  "texts": [
    "• Student-exercise interactions are the fundamental input for student cognitive modeling.",
    "It encompasses common features such as correctness labels, answering textual content, and interaction timestamp.",
    "In addition, some studies [29][30][31] also design diverse forgetting features via interaction timestamp to capture students' forgetting characteristics.",
    "• Exercise-side features refer to the content information of exercises.",
    "This includes various modalities such as textual descriptions, images, and other multimedia elements associated with the exercises."
  ],
